of their chosen way of imitating Christ was fought with defiant conviction, and the book includes the first annotated English translation of the biography of Alexander Akoimetos (Alexander the Sleepless). Wandering, Begging Monks allows us to understand these fascinating figures of early Christianity in the full context of late Roman society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMessalians. 0aMonastic and religious lifexHistoryxEarly church, ca. 30-600. 0aMonastic and religious lifexHistoryyEarly church, ca. 30-600. 7aRELIGION / Antiquities & Archaeology.2bisacsh  a4th century.  a5th century.  aalexander akoimetos.  aalexander the sleepless.  aantiquity.  aapostolic.  aascetic.  aasia minor.  aaugustine.  abegging.  acatholic church.  acatholicism.  achristian poverty.  achurch history.  acloister.  adevotions.  aearly christianity.  aearly church.  aegypt.  aepiscopal authority.  agospels.  ahomelessness.  ahomilies.  amaterial renunciation.  amonasticism.  amonks.  aon the work of monks.  apatronage.  apseudo clementine letters to virgins.  areligious life.  areligious vows.  aroman empire.  asocial history.  aspiritual life.  asyria.  avow of poverty.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092850340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520928503423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520928503/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles